Baleen whales: Pygmy blue, humpback, southern right whale

Shelf pelagic sharks: White, bronze & dusky whaler sharks, blue shark

Shelf demersal sharks: Whiskery shark, broadnose shark, Port Jackson shark, carpet, wobbegong, saw shark, cat shark

Skates and rays: Melbourne skate, southern fiddler ray, southern shovelnose ray, smooth stingray, coastal stingaree

Tunas and billfish: Frigate mackerel, skipjack tuna, albacore tuna, yellowfin tuna, bonito, bigeye tuna, billfish, striped marlin

Offshore pelagic piscivores: Ray's bream, southern Ray's bream, moonfish, oilfish, short sunfish, trevallas, rudderfish

Offshore pelagic invertivores large: Large pelagic species feeding primarily on invertebrates

Shelf large pelagic piscivores: Australian salmon, herring, barracouta, long-fin pike, tommy rough, tailor, snook

Anchovy and other small pelagics: Engraulis australis and other small planktivorous fish

Shelf small demersal piscivores: Small demersal fish feeding primarily on other fish

Shelf small demersal omnivores: Small demersal fish with varied diet

Shelf large demersal piscivores: Large demersal fish feeding primarily on other fish

Shelf large demersal omnivores: Large demersal fish with varied diet

Slope small demersal invertivores: Small demersal fish feeding on invertebrates in slope waters

Slope small demersal piscivores: Small demersal fish feeding on fish in slope waters

Slope large demersal piscivores: Large demersal fish feeding on fish in slope waters

Slope large demersal omnivores: Large demersal fish with varied diet in slope waters

Benthic detritivore: Infaunal detritivores including polychaetes, sipunculids, burrowing bivalves

Benthic carnivores (infauna): Infaunal carnivores/scavengers including echinoderms, gastropods, predatory polychaetes

Meiobenthos: Small benthic organisms living in sediments < 1 mm

Shelf filter feeders: Sessile megafauna on the shelf including bivalves, sponges, bryozoans

Deep filter feeders: Sessile megafauna beyond shelf break including deep-sea corals, anemones

Shelf macrozoobenthos: Large, active, primarily carnivorous megafauna on the shelf

Squid & cuttlefish shelf: Southern calamari, Australian giant cuttlefish and other shelf cephalopods

Crabs & bugs: Blue crabs, sand crabs, Balmain bugs, other crabs

Deep macrozoobenthos: Large, active, primarily carnivorous megafauna in deep waters

Gelatinous zooplankton: Jellyfish, pyrosomes, medusa, salps and ctenophores

Large zooplankton: 2-20 cm Euphausiids, mysids, copepods and amphipods

Mesozooplankton: 0.2-2 cm zooplankton including copepods, pteropods, ostracods
